When generating hashtags for {{ domain_name | title }} content, follow these rules:

1. Include 1–2 broad reach tags (e.g. #B2BSales, #SaaS, #OutboundSales)
2. Include 1–2 niche or intent-specific tags that match the email topic or target industry
3. Maximum {{ max_tags }} hashtags per output
4. No single hashtag longer than 30 characters
5. Use CamelCase for multi-word tags (#ColdEmail, not #coldemail or #cold_email)
6. Never embed statistics, pricing, or product claims inside a hashtag
7. Platform defaults — apply unless the user specifies otherwise:
   - LinkedIn: 3–5 tags (quality over quantity)
   - Twitter / X: 1–2 tags (inline, not appended)
   - Instagram: up to 10 tags (first comment preferred)
8. Avoid generic filler tags (#Marketing, #Business) unless paired with a more specific one
